        {{/* API Documentation */}}
        <section id="api-docs" class="help-section api-docs">
            <h2>API Documentation</h2>
            <p>This application provides full REST and GraphQL APIs with interactive documentation.</p>
            <div class="api-links">
                <a href="/openapi" class="api-link-card">
                    <h3>OpenAPI / Swagger</h3>
                    <p>Interactive REST API explorer with try-it-out functionality</p>
                </a>
                <a href="/graphql" class="api-link-card">
                    <h3>GraphQL Playground</h3>
                    <p>Interactive GraphQL explorer with schema documentation</p>
                </a>
            </div>

            <h3>API Endpoints</h3>
            <table class="operators-table">
                <thead>
                    <tr><th>Method</th><th>Endpoint</th><th>Description</th></tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/api/v1/search</code></td>
                        <td>JSON search results</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/api/v1/autocomplete</code></td>
                        <td>Search suggestions</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/api/v1/instant</code></td>
                        <td>Instant answers</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/api/v1/engines</code></td>
                        <td>Available engines and status</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/api/v1/categories</code></td>
                        <td>Search categories</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/api/v1/bangs</code></td>
                        <td>Available bang shortcuts</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/opensearch.xml</code></td>
                        <td>OpenSearch descriptor</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><code>GET</code></td>
                        <td><code>/search.rss</code></td>
                        <td>Search results as RSS feed</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <h3>Example: Search API</h3>
            <p class="api-note">Replace <code>$SERVER</code> with your server URL (e.g., <code>{{if .Config.Server.BaseURL}}{{.Config.Server.BaseURL}}{{else}}https://search.example.com{{end}}</code>)</p>
            <pre class="code-block"><code># Search for "golang tutorial"
curl "$SERVER/api/v1/search?q=golang+tutorial&category=general"

# Image search with safe search
curl "$SERVER/api/v1/search?q=nature&category=images&safe=moderate"

# Get autocomplete suggestions
curl "$SERVER/api/v1/autocomplete?q=pyth"</code></pre>

            <h3>Example: Instant Answers</h3>
            <pre class="code-block"><code># Calculator
curl "$SERVER/api/v1/instant?q=sqrt(144)"

# Weather
curl "$SERVER/api/v1/instant?q=weather+tokyo"

# IP lookup
curl "$SERVER/api/v1/instant?q=ip:8.8.8.8"</code></pre>

            <h3>Example: RSS Feed</h3>
            <pre class="code-block"><code># Get search results as RSS
curl "$SERVER/search.rss?q=linux+news"</code></pre>
        </section>

        {{/* Privacy Features */}}
        <section id="privacy" class="help-section">
            <h2>Privacy Features</h2>
            <ul class="privacy-list">
                <li><strong>No tracking:</strong> We don't track your searches or create user profiles</li>
                <li><strong>No search history:</strong> Your searches are not stored on our servers</li>
                <li><strong>Tor support:</strong> Access via Tor hidden service for maximum anonymity{{if .Config.Server.Tor.Enabled}} (<a href="#tor-access">see below</a>){{end}}</li>
                <li><strong>Minimal cookies:</strong> Only essential cookies for preferences (no analytics)</li>
                <li><strong>No JavaScript required:</strong> Core search works without JavaScript</li>
                <li><strong>Open source:</strong> Full source code available for audit</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        {{/* Tor Access - only shown if Tor is enabled */}}
        {{if .Config.Server.Tor.Enabled}}
        <section id="tor-access" class="help-section tor-access">
            <h2>Tor Access</h2>
            <p>This application is available as a Tor hidden service for enhanced privacy.</p>

            {{if .TorAddress}}
            <h3>Onion Address</h3>
            <div class="onion-address-box">
                <code id="onion-addr" class="onion-address">{{.TorAddress}}</code>
                <button class="btn-copy" data-copy-target="onion-addr" aria-label="Copy to clipboard">
                    <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                        <rect x="9" y="9" width="13" height="13" rx="2" ry="2"></rect>
                        <path d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"></path>
                    </svg>
                    Copy
                </button>
            </div>
            {{else}}
            <p class="tor-note">Tor address will be available once the hidden service connects to the Tor network.</p>
            {{end}}

            <h3>How to Connect</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Download <a href="https://www.torproject.org/download/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tor Browser</a></li>
                <li>Open Tor Browser and wait for it to connect</li>
                <li>Copy the onion address above and paste it into the Tor Browser address bar</li>
            </ol>

            <p class="tor-note">Using Tor provides additional privacy by hiding your IP address and encrypting your connection through the Tor network.</p>
        </section>
        {{end}}

        {{/* FAQ */}}
        <section id="faq" class="help-section">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <details>
                    <summary>Why are results different from Google?</summary>
                    <p>We aggregate results from multiple sources without personalization. Results aren't filtered based on your history, location, or profile, so they may differ from what you see on personalized search engines.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How do I access via Tor?</summary>
                    <p>Install <a href="https://www.torproject.org/download/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tor Browser</a> and use our .onion address.{{if .Config.Server.Tor.Enabled}} See the <a href="#tor-access">Tor Access section</a> above for the address and instructions.{{end}}</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Can I self-host this?</summary>
                    <p>Yes! This is free and open source software.{{if .Config.Server.Branding.SourceCodeURL}} Check our <a href="{{.Config.Server.Branding.SourceCodeURL}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">source code repository</a> for installation instructions.{{end}}</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>What search engines do you use?</summary>
                    <p>We aggregate results from multiple sources including DuckDuckGo, Brave Search, Wikipedia, and specialized engines for images, videos, and news.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How do instant answers work?</summary>
                    <p>Instant answers are generated locally for common queries like calculations, conversions, and definitions. They don't require external API calls.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </section>

        {{/* Need Help */}}
        <section class="help-section">
            <h2>Need More Help?</h2>
            <p>If you have questions or need assistance, please <a href="/server/contact">contact us</a>.</p>
        </section>
    </div>
    {{end}}
</div>
{{end}}
